===================================================================
[3] INDEPENDENT INERT-BY-DEFAULT PROOF (binary equivalence)
===================================================================
Method: compile pristine + patched glm.c to objects; disassemble; normalize
absolute addresses; compare machine code PER FUNCTION. The new KaE* field is
APPENDED to struct Model, so every pre-existing field offset is preserved.

shared functions compared : 92
BYTE-IDENTICAL machine code: 88  (95%)
functions that CHANGED     : ['layer_forward', 'main', 'model_init', 'moe']
new function (KaE-only)     : ['kae_free.part.0']

Why each changed function changed (NONE is a behavioural change when KAE is unset):
  model_init: sole delta = ['-mov    $0x6278,%edx', '+mov    $0x6280,%edx']
              = sizeof(Model) 0x6278->0x6280 (the appended 8-byte KaE* field); NO logic change
  layer_forward: passes the already-computed pos_base into moe() (register plumbing)
  moe: adds ONE guarded tail branch (source below)
  main: adds KaE env-parse + kae_load + KAE_SCORE dispatch, all under if(getenv/g_kae)

Source of the sole moe() insertion (guard chain; skipped entirely when g_kae==0):
    if(g_kae && m->kae) kae_apply_add(m->kae, layer, pos_base, S, D, out);
and kae_apply_add returns immediately unless mode==0 AND the layer is a splice layer.
So with KAE unset (g_kae==0, the engine default) the branch is NOT taken and every
computed activation is byte-identical to upstream — consistent with the 88/92 result.

